  "prompt": "What is the meaning of \"I envy you\"?",
  "response": "The phrase \"I envy you\" is used to express that someone wishes they had something that another person possesses, whether it be a quality, possession, situation, or experience. It conveys a sense of admiration mixed with a desire to have what the other person has. It can be used both sincerely and lightheartedly, depending on the context.",
